io.hekate.cluster.seed.jdbc

Class JdbcSeedNodeProviderConfig

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.hekate.cluster.seed.jdbc.JdbcSeedNodeProviderConfig

  • public class JdbcSeedNodeProviderConfig
extends Object
    Configuration for JdbcSeedNodeProvider.

    Database structure

    By default the following database table should exist in the target database: 

    
 CREATE TABLE cluster_nodes (
      cluster_name VARCHAR,
      host VARCHAR,
      port NUMBER
 )

    It is possible to modify table and column names by using the following properties:

    • setTable(String) - table name (default is "cluster_nodes")
    • setClusterColumn(String) - name of a column to store cluster name (default is "cluster_name")
    • setHostColumn(String) - name of a column to store host address (default is "host")
    • setPortColumn(String) - name of a column to store port value (default is "port")

    Database connectivity

    Database connectivity is controlled by the following properties:

    • setDataSource(DataSource) - JDBC datasource to be used for obtaining database connections
    • setQueryTimeout(int) - optional timeout value for SQL queries (see Statement.setQueryTimeout(int))
    See Also:
